  "prompt": "What is cognition?",
  "response": "Cognition refers to the mental processes and abilities involved in acquiring, processing, storing, and using information. It encompasses a wide range of functions including perception, attention, memory, learning, reasoning, problem-solving, decision making, and language comprehension and production. Cognition is essential for understanding and interacting with the world around us, and it plays a crucial role in shaping our thoughts, behaviors, and emotions. It is studied in various disciplines, including psychology, neuroscience, philosophy, and computer science.",
